  <p>
    Dr. Ryan Topping and Victor Carpay were recently invited to attend the FINE Gathering
    in Ottawa, an event coordinated by Catholic Christian Outreach (CCO). The gathering
    brought together Catholic leaders from across the country for a time of fellowship,
    discussion, and shared vision for the future of the Church in Canada.
  </p>

  <p>
    While in Ottawa, Dr. Topping and Victor were also invited to the National Prayer Breakfast
    by MP Shuv Majumbar, representing the riding of Calgary Heritage. The Prayer Breakfast
    is an annual, non-partisan gathering of parliamentarians and community leaders who come
    together in a spirit of prayer and national reflection.
  </p>

  <p>
    These gatherings represent an important opportunity for the Gregory the Great Institute
    to build relationships with other Catholic organizations and public servants who share
    a commitment to faith, culture, and the common good. As the Institute grows, events like
    these help to establish the kind of network that will be essential for renewing Catholic
    culture at the national level.
  </p>

  <p>
    We are grateful for the invitation and look forward to continued collaboration with
    CCO and the many faithful leaders we met in Ottawa.
  </p>
